<div id="sub-page">
<h2>Destination Poland</h2>
<p>Poland is a perfect place to invest in, and a great place to develop your business. The geographical location of Poland which borders with both the European Union countries (Germany, Czech Republic, Slovakia, Lithuania) and Eastern European countries (Ukraine, Belarus, Russia) means that it has access to 250 million consumers in the radius of 1000 km. In the latest Ernst&amp;Young European Attractiveness Survey 2010 report Poland was indicated by managers of international companies as a location of new direct overseas investments in Europe (BIZ) most often considered.</p>
<p>Poland is where West- East and North-South transit routes meet. The network of roads and motorways, growing each year, numerous airports and access to sea influence logistics, and thus economy, positively.</p>
<p>Polish economy has solid foundation for stable development. The global economic crisis did not do much harm to Poland which &ndash; as the only country in Europe &ndash; did not suffer from recession, what is more, it developed at the highest pace on the continent. Stability and safety, guaranteed by membership in the EU and NATO make Poland a trustworthy and competitive business partner for foreign investors.</p>
<p>Experts in numerous fields of science and economy graduate from Polish universities each year. There are almost two million students here. High level of teaching makes them a perfect personnel base for business entities.</p>
<p>Poland, being the sixth largest country of the European Union in respect of number of residents, constitutes a huge market for goods and services.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
